282
00:22:11,415 --> 00:22:13,750
-Her dad will be...
-Nope. Nope.

283
00:22:13,917 --> 00:22:16,211
...super disappointed in her.

284
00:22:16,295 --> 00:22:17,129
Stop it.

285
00:22:17,212 --> 00:22:19,882
He might even be ashamed.

286
00:22:20,048 --> 00:22:21,008
What are you doing?

287
00:22:21,175 --> 00:22:22,342
But the main thing is...

288
00:22:22,509 --> 00:22:25,971
if her father can't retire,
it will be all Ember's...

289
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:27,681
Stop talking!

290
00:22:40,152 --> 00:22:42,821
Looks like I'm going home early today.

291
00:22:42,988 --> 00:22:43,989
No, don't.

292
00:22:45,657 --> 00:22:48,785
Expect to get shut down within a week.

293
00:22:48,952 --> 00:22:49,786
Have a good one.

294
00:22:53,290 --> 00:22:54,750
Sorry.

295
00:23:01,006 --> 00:23:02,007
What?

296
00:23:03,091 --> 00:23:04,092
Already?

297
00:23:04,801 --> 00:23:05,802
Hello?

298
00:23:17,147 --> 00:23:18,023
Oh, no.

299
00:23:18,106 --> 00:23:19,483
Dad, what happened?

300
00:23:19,650 --> 00:23:22,945
We lucky nobody hurt.
It ruined Red Dot Sale.

301
00:23:23,111 --> 00:23:24,655
-Did he do this?
-Who?

302
00:23:24,821 --> 00:23:26,823
The Water guy I see you chase.

303
00:23:29,826 --> 00:23:30,994
Yeah, he did.

304
00:23:31,954 --> 00:23:34,581
He just broke through a pipe.
I don't know why.

305
00:23:34,748 --> 00:23:38,210
Luckily, I was able to close it off.
I couldn't catch him though.

306
00:23:38,377 --> 00:23:40,879
Water, always trying to water us down.

307
00:23:41,046 --> 00:23:44,091
He was a Water person, Dad, not just water.

308
00:23:44,383 --> 00:23:46,593
Same thing.
And why is water in pipes?

309
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:50,597
City shut down years ago.
There should be no water.

310
00:23:51,598 --> 00:23:52,432
Dad!

311
00:23:54,101 --> 00:23:55,102
Bernie.

312
00:23:55,561 --> 00:23:56,687
We will get through this.

313
00:23:56,854 --> 00:23:58,146
Just like before.

314
00:23:58,480 --> 00:23:59,565
Before?

315
00:24:00,023 --> 00:24:02,359
There is a reason we left Fire Land.

316
00:24:03,193 --> 00:24:06,280
Ember, we loved it there so much.

317
00:24:07,114 --> 00:24:09,491
Most everyone had a Blue Flame.

318
00:24:09,658 --> 00:24:11,910
And it connected us all together.

319
00:24:12,327 --> 00:24:15,038
To our traditions. Our family.

320
00:24:15,205 --> 00:24:17,040
<i>It was hard living.</i>

321
00:24:17,207 --> 00:24:20,085
<i>But your father began to build a life for us.</i>

322
00:24:20,252 --> 00:24:22,004
<i>We put everything into it.</i>

323
00:24:22,421 --> 00:24:24,423
<i>But then a great storm came.</i>

324
00:24:35,934 --> 00:24:37,895
<i>All was lost for us.</i>

325
00:24:38,812 --> 00:24:43,817
<i>Your father understood
we had to leave everything.</i>

326
00:24:43,984 --> 00:24:48,238
<i>Our home. It was the only way
to create a better life.</i>

327
00:24:57,331 --> 00:25:00,876
<i>It was the last time
your father ever saw his family.</i>

328
00:25:03,295 --> 00:25:05,506
That is why we came here.

329
00:25:05,672 --> 00:25:07,508
To build all this.

330
00:25:13,931 --> 00:25:18,852
