-Yay!
-Yeah! Way to go, Lutz!

398
00:29:37,402 --> 00:29:38,946
Yeah, Lutz!

399
00:29:39,112 --> 00:29:40,614
That was amazing, Lutz!

400
00:29:42,658 --> 00:29:44,910
Yeah! Yeah! Yes!

401
00:29:55,921 --> 00:29:57,506
What a comeback.

402
00:29:57,673 --> 00:30:00,342
Check out who found the gift shop.

403
00:30:00,926 --> 00:30:03,262
I gotta admit, that was pretty cool.

404
00:30:03,428 --> 00:30:05,806
You can see why I can get all churned up...

405
00:30:05,973 --> 00:30:09,560
but as a cloud puff who used to
come here with her dad...

406
00:30:09,726 --> 00:30:11,895
all these wins mean a little bit more.

407
00:30:12,062 --> 00:30:15,691
And as a fireball who's supposed
to take over her dad's shop...

408
00:30:15,858 --> 00:30:19,027
I sure don't want to let him down,
and I could use a win, too.

409
00:30:20,571 --> 00:30:22,614
Now, I just got to stop water
from coming in.

410
00:30:22,781 --> 00:30:25,200
-Water? In Firetown?
-Yeah.

411
00:30:25,367 --> 00:30:27,202
Water was shut off to there years ago.

412
00:30:27,369 --> 00:30:28,203
Forget the tickets...

413
00:30:28,370 --> 00:30:32,332
I'm gonna have to take apart your dad's shop
to figure out what's going on.

414
00:30:32,499 --> 00:30:33,500
You can't!

415
00:30:33,667 --> 00:30:36,420
My dad put his whole life into that place.

416
00:30:36,587 --> 00:30:38,964
I bet this is connected
to that fluffing leak.

417
00:30:39,339 --> 00:30:41,884
Yeah, we've been trying
to track down a leak in the city.

418
00:30:42,050 --> 00:30:43,552
It's why I was in the canal and...

419
00:30:43,719 --> 00:30:47,014
Wait, I know where
I got sucked into Ember's shop.

420
00:30:47,181 --> 00:30:51,101
Ember and I could track the water
from her shop to find the source of the leak.

421
00:30:51,435 --> 00:30:52,519
Keep talking.

422
00:30:52,686 --> 00:30:55,189
I could call in a city crew
to fix whatever we find.

423
00:30:55,355 --> 00:30:59,026
Yes. And there'd be no need
to touch my dad's shop.

424
00:31:01,278 --> 00:31:02,779
You're lucky you're a cute couple.

425
00:31:03,155 --> 00:31:03,989
We're not a...

426
00:31:04,156 --> 00:31:05,032
You got until Friday.

427
00:31:05,199 --> 00:31:08,327
If you can find the leak
and get a crew to fix it by then...

428
00:31:08,493 --> 00:31:09,745
those tickets are forgiven.

429
00:31:09,912 --> 00:31:13,665
If not, your dad's shop gets shut down.

430
00:31:14,917 --> 00:31:17,252
Break wind! Break wind!

431
00:31:17,419 --> 00:31:18,420
Thank you.

432
00:31:21,423 --> 00:31:23,467
-Please take all that off.
-But I got you a hat.

433
00:31:27,429 --> 00:31:29,181
Okay.

434
00:31:29,932 --> 00:31:33,352
Just keep out of sight, okay?
It'd be a whole thing.

435
00:31:33,519 --> 00:31:35,103
Now water upstairs?

436
00:31:36,146 --> 00:31:37,272
It's in the walls.

437
00:31:37,439 --> 00:31:41,193
I don't understand.
I fix one pipe and another one leaks.

438
00:31:41,693 --> 00:31:42,694
Water!

439
00:31:45,781 --> 00:31:46,865
How could it be worse?

440
00:31:47,032 --> 00:31:50,827
Now that the water's back, the pressure
is forcing it up to all your pipes.

441
00:31:50,994 --> 00:31:52,538
We gotta find the source.

442
00:31:53,163 --> 00:31:54,748
How did you even end up here?

443
00:31:55,541 --> 00:31:59,086
Well, I was in the canals
checking the doors for leaks...

444
00:31:59,253 --> 00:32:01,421
<i>when I found some water
that shouldn't have been there.</i>

445
00:32:02,339 --> 00:32:05,259
Rusty with a hint of motor oil?

446
00:32:06,426 --> 00:32:07,803
<i>There was this whoosh of water.</i>

447
00:32:09,054 --> 00:32:10,931
<i>And I got sucked into a filtering system.</i>

448
00:32:11,098 --> 00:32:12,099
Help!

449
00:32:12,599 --> 00:32:14,726
<i>But then I heard this explosion.</i>

450
00:32:19,147 --> 00:32:20,941
<i>That's how I ended up at your place.</i>

451
00:32:21,149 --> 00:32:24,069
Oh, flame! My temper caused this.

452
00:32:24,236 --> 00:32:27,072
So, we're searching for water
somewhere in a canal?

453
00:32:27,406 --> 00:32:29,116
Those canals go everywhere.

454
00:32:29,283 --> 00:32:32,327
It's why tracking down that leak
has been so dang hard.

455
00:32:32,494 --> 00:32:33,328
The roof.

456
00:32:41,503 --> 00:32:43,005
You might want to step back.

457
00:32:49,219 --> 00:32:50,888
Holy dew drop!

458
00:32:51,763 --> 00:32:52,764
Get in.

459
00:33:18,248 --> 00:33:19,958
Okay, that's where I got sucked in.

460
00:33:21,502 --> 00:33:23,504
More water.
Go that way.

461
00:33:29,426 --> 00:33:30,469
Yeah, right there.

462
00:33:32,930 --> 00:33:34,306
Nothing weird going on here.

463
00:33:34,765 --> 00:33:36,642
Just a little pruning.

464
00:33:51,532 --> 00:33:55,452
So, what do you do at the shop?
If you don't mind me asking.

465
00:33:55,619 --> 00:33:58,121
My dad's retiring and I'll be taking over.

466
00:33:58,288 --> 00:33:59,289
Someday.

467
00:34:00,415 --> 00:34:01,583
When I'm ready.

468
00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:03,669
It must be nice knowing what you're gonna do.

469
00:34:03,836 --> 00:34:06,380
After my dad passed,
I got all, "What's the point?"

470
00:34:06,755 --> 00:34:08,799
Now I just go from one job to the next.

471
00:34:09,550 --> 00:34:11,176
There's a word in Firish.

472
00:34:11,552 --> 00:34:12,594
<i>Tìshók.</i>

473
00:34:13,094 --> 00:34:16,931
It means embrace the light while it burns
because it won't always last forever.

474
00:34:17,850 --> 00:34:21,143
Tee-shook.

475
00:34:21,812 --> 00:34:23,188
Or something like that.

476
00:34:28,777 --> 00:34:30,696
-You okay?
-Yeah.

477
00:34:30,862 --> 00:34:31,864
You sure?

478
00:34:32,781 --> 00:34:35,826
It's just, that building over there...

479
00:34:36,284 --> 00:34:38,078
that's Garden Central Station.

480
00:34:38,661 --> 00:34:43,292
When I was a kid, my dad took me there
because they had a Vivisteria tree.

481
00:34:44,251 --> 00:34:46,460
<i>I'd always wanted to see one.</i>

482
00:34:47,129 --> 00:34:49,922
<i>It's the only flower that can thrive
in any environment.</i>

483
00:34:51,842 --> 00:34:53,010
<i>Fire included.</i>

484
00:34:54,011 --> 00:34:55,888
<i>I was so excited.</i>

485
00:34:56,054 --> 00:34:58,182
<i>But they said our fire was too dangerous...</i>

486
00:34:59,141 --> 00:35:00,475
<i>and they wouldn't let us in.</i>

487
00:35:01,935 --> 00:35:03,520
Go back to Fire Land.

488
00:35:03,687 --> 00:35:05,147
<i>My dad was so angry...</i>

489
00:35:05,314 --> 00:35:07,482
-Burn somewhere else!
-Get outta here!

490
00:35:07,566 --> 00:35:08,859
<i>...and embarrassed.</i>

491
00:35:09,484 --> 00:35:11,445
The building flooded a few years later.

492
00:35:11,612 --> 00:35:14,448
So, I missed my one chance
to see a Vivisteria.

493
00:35:18,702 --> 00:35:20,662
You must have been so scared.

494
00:35:22,748 --> 00:35:23,874
I was.

495
00:35:26,251 --> 00:35:27,419
How do you do that?

496
00:35:27,586 --> 00:35:29,338
-Do what?
-Draw people in?

497
00:35:29,505 --> 00:35:31,507
You got a whole stadium to connect with you.

498
00:35:32,049 --> 00:35:34,593
I can't even connect with one customer.

499
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:36,637
My stupid temper always kicks in.

500
00:35:36,803 --> 00:35:39,389
I guess I just say what I feel.

501
00:35:39,556 --> 00:35:41,433
And I don't think a temper is so bad.

502
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:43,477
Sometimes when I lose my temper...

503
00:35:43,644 --> 00:35:47,022
I think it's just me trying
to tell me something I'm not ready to hear.

504
00:35:47,189 --> 00:35:48,941
That's ridiculous.

505
00:35:49,107 --> 00:35:50,108
Maybe.

506
00:35:50,859 --> 00:35:51,777
Hey, there.

507
00:35:51,944 --> 00:35:53,111
Put us down there.

508
00:35:58,951 --> 00:36:00,244
That's not right.

509
00:36:03,747 --> 00:36:04,706
Motor oil.

510
00:36:04,873 --> 00:36:06,542
Yup, this is the source.

511
00:36:07,835 --> 00:36:08,877
Why is there no water?

512
00:36:09,044 --> 00:36:10,420
Because the doors are broken.

513
00:36:10,587 --> 00:36:14,174
This is supposed to catch spill over
from those main canals and...

514
00:36:19,638 --> 00:36:20,889
Run for your life!

515
00:36:25,894 --> 00:36:27,062
Help!

516
00:36:30,774 --> 00:36:31,608
Grab this!

517
00:36:40,534 --> 00:36:41,368
Firetown.

518
00:36:50,294 --> 00:36:51,295
Catch!

519
00:37:14,443 --> 00:37:16,570
